Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Cut the @red cabbage{1} in half lengthways, remove the triangle root in the middle, then slice thinly. Trim the @green beans{80}. Halve the @plums{2} and remove the stone. Put the plums on a large lined #baking tray{} and set aside. Put a #saucepan{} of water on a high heat to boil.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on a medium heat. When hot, add the red onion and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @ground cinnamon{1} and start anise and stir through. Add the @red wine vinegar{1%star anise}(and stir well. Stir well and cook stirring often until the water has evaporated and the cabbage is tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging and place on the same tray as the plums (skin side up). Pop on the top shelf of your oven and roast until golden and crispy, ~{25-30%mins}. Meanwhile, peel the @potatoes{450%g} and chop into 2cm chunks. Add to the saucepan of boiling water with @salt{0.5%tsp} and cook until tender, ~{18-20%mins}. Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @milk{} (if you have some). Mash the potato until smooth using a #potato masher{}, season well with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

When the duck has 10 mins left, put the green beans on the #baking tray{} alongside the plums and cook in the oven for the remaining time. Once cooked, remove the star anise from your cabbage. Stir the @redcurrant jelly{25%ml} through, taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

In a small saucepan bring the @water{150%ml} to the boil, add the @red wine jus paste{1} and stir well to dissolve. Cook until thick enough to coat the back of a #spoon{}, ~{5-7%mins}. Remove from the heat.

Reheat the cabbage and mash if necessary. Share the mash between your plates, followed by the red cabbage. Place a duck leg on each plate and share the beans and plums among yourselves. Spoon over the sauce and enjoy!

> We love good Confit Duck Leg with Mash, Spiced Red Cabbage & Roast Plums and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!